body:
@ncw , I think I found the culprit: We need to pull the client creation into each writeAt, as the client is forced to only hold a single TCP connection, which may be unstable for larger files.
But at the same time, this increases the overhead for each writeAt, so I would really love to increase the default bufferSize (IMHO even to the same as chunkSize). But I don't see an easy way to do that with OpenWriterAt, any hints there? 
Otherwise we would need to switch to OpenChunkWriter...
